Upon registering with Synergy Chat each  account will create users as well as groups for their account and then will select their chat button. The chat button is a unique code for each Synergy Chat account and only shows the users/groups that were created upon registering.
    		 When a Synergy Chat member or a guest click on the chat button the guest interface will appear showing the online and offline users of the respective account. A Synergy Chat member simply clicks on the member login button on the top right of the interface to login to the member interface. A guest simply clicks on any available name/group on the list of the guest interface and will be prompted to enter their name as well as email address to begin communicating. 
    		It may sound confusing but is actually very simple. Using the guest interface once or twice is all it takes to understand how it works.
          
